  <section class="s16-featured" id="featured-decision" aria-labelledby="featured-title"><div class="shell"><div class="s16-section-heading"><p class="s16-eyebrow">FEATURED DECISION</p><p>Choose the depth that fits the moment.</p></div><article class="s16-decision-intro"><p class="s16-topic">COMPENSATION</p><h2 id="featured-title">Are you getting paid what you’re worth?</h2><p>See the compensation formula most physicians never receive—and what to ask for before your next conversation.</p></article><div class="s16-depths" id="questions" aria-label="Decision learning depths"><button type="button" class="s16-depth-card" data-pathway="big"><span>BIG PICTURE</span><strong>30 seconds</strong><p>See what matters</p><b>Open pathway →</b></button><button type="button" class="s16-depth-card s16-depth-card--primary" data-pathway="brief"><span>BRIEF OVERVIEW</span><strong>2 minutes</strong><p>Understand the formula</p><b>Open pathway →</b></button><button type="button" class="s16-depth-card" data-pathway="deep"><span>DEEP DIVE</span><strong>5 minutes</strong><p>Apply it to your situation</p><b>Open pathway →</b></button></div></div></section>

  <section class="s17-pathway" id="compensation-pathway" hidden aria-live="polite"><div class="shell s17-content"><nav class="s17-path-nav" aria-label="Compensation pathway"><button type="button" data-pathway="big">Big Picture</button><button type="button" data-pathway="brief">Brief Overview</button><button type="button" data-pathway="deep">Deep Dive</button></nav><div class="s17-path-content">
    <article data-path-content="big"><p class="s16-eyebrow">BIG PICTURE · 30 SECONDS</p><h2>Compensation is a formula—not a headline.</h2><div class="s17-formula"><b>COMPENSATION =</b><span>GUARANTEE</span><i>+</i><span>PRODUCTIVITY</span><i>+</i><span>QUALITY</span><i>+</i><span>CALL / LEADERSHIP</span><i>−</i><span class="condition">UNSEEN CONDITIONS</span></div><ol class="s17-questions"><li>What threshold must you clear?</li><li>What is the conversion factor?</li><li>What work is attributed to you?</li></ol><p class="s17-action"><strong>Ask now:</strong> Ask for the complete written formula and the last two reconciliation statements.</p></article>
    <article data-path-content="brief" hidden><p class="s16-eyebrow">BRIEF OVERVIEW · 2 MINUTES</p><h2>Same salary can mean very different economics.</h2><div class="s17-comparison"><div><span>Offer A</span><b>$300k</b><p>Low threshold, clear attribution, quarterly reconciliation.</p></div><div><span>Offer B</span><b>$300k</b><p>High threshold, exclusions, annual reconciliation.</p></div></div><dl class="s17-definition-list"><dt>Threshold</dt><dd>The production level required before incentive pay begins.</dd><dt>Conversion factor</dt><dd>The amount paid for each credited unit above the threshold.</dd><dt>Attribution</dt><dd>Which work is credited to you—and which work is excluded.</dd><dt>Quality adjustments</dt><dd>The measures, weights, and timing that can change payment.</dd><dt>Reconciliation</dt><dd>How often the employer compares estimates to actual results and corrects payment.</dd></dl><h3>Three-question checklist</h3><ol class="s17-questions"><li>Can you show the formula, definitions, and exclusions in writing?</li><li>Can you show two recent reconciliations for this role?</li><li>Who resolves an attribution or quality-measure dispute?</li></ol></article>
    <article data-path-content="deep" hidden><p class="s16-eyebrow">DEEP DIVE · 5 MINUTES</p><h2>Apply the formula before the conversation.</h2><div class="s17-deep-grid"><section><h3>Worked example</h3><p>A $300,000 guarantee includes 5,000 wRVUs. At 6,000 credited wRVUs and a $55 conversion factor, illustrative productivity pay is $55,000 before quality, call, and contract-specific adjustments.</p><h3>Negotiation sequence</h3><ol><li>Request the written formula and definitions.</li><li>Compare a recent reconciliation with your expected work.</li><li>Clarify attribution, quality, call, and timing.</li><li>Ask for any agreed changes in the contract.</li></ol><h3>Common traps</h3><ul><li>Assuming the headline salary is the full formula.</li><li>Missing excluded work or changing benchmarks.</li><li>Accepting undefined quality measures or delayed reconciliation.</li></ul></section><section class="s17-calculator"><h3>Illustrative calculator</h3><label>Guaranteed compensation <input data-calc="guarantee" type="number" value="300000" min="0"></label><label>Credited wRVUs <input data-calc="units" type="number" value="6000" min="0"></label><label>Threshold wRVUs <input data-calc="threshold" type="number" value="5000" min="0"></label><label>Conversion factor <input data-calc="factor" type="number" value="55" min="0"></label><output data-calculator-result>Illustrative total: $355,000</output><small>Educational illustration only; terms and payment rules vary.</small></section></div><section class="s17-contract"><h3>Educational sample contract language</h3><blockquote>“The employer will provide the productivity formula, applicable threshold, conversion factor, attribution rules, quality measures, and reconciliation schedule in writing.”</blockquote></section><label class="s17-checklist"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> I saved the question checklist for my next conversation.</label><button type="button" class="s16-button s17-download" data-download-checklist>Download checklist</button><button type="button" class="s16-text-button s17-confidence-update" data-confidence-update>Update confidence</button><section class="s17-knowledge"><h3>Knowledge check</h3><p>Which item most directly determines when productivity pay begins?</p><button type="button" data-knowledge="wrong">The headline guarantee</button><button type="button" data-knowledge="correct">The stated threshold</button><button type="button" data-knowledge="wrong">The job title</button><p data-knowledge-result></p></section><section class="s17-feedback"><h3>Was this useful?</h3><button type="button" data-feedback="yes">Yes</button><button type="button" data-feedback="no">Not yet</button><p data-feedback-result></p></section><p class="s17-disclaimer">Educational information, not legal, tax, financial, or employment advice. Have a qualified professional review your specific agreement.</p><p class="s17-references"><strong>References:</strong> <a href="https://www.ama-assn.org/practice-management/physician-health/physician-contracts-what-know" target="_blank" rel="noopener">American Medical Association: physician contracts</a> · <a href="https://www.cms.gov/medicare/payment/fee-schedules/physician" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CMS Physician Fee Schedule</a></p></article>
